{
  "stem": "25773.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "After [INAUDIBLE] they got an injection, and-- and they got rid of them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "But the young were taken to different camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "To extermination camps or to-- or to working place, or to the motherland to work for the war efforts.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "So the selection took place every day at a certain hour, and the big lorry came.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "The Germans came, and all too familiar for me, for us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And taking the young people, a cousin of mine, went to Belsen-Bergen this way and another friend went to another camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And as we have watched the procedure of these things, we always retreated to the toilets, and we pretended to be busy and cleaning there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And each time it took her like an hour or half hour, we came back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And so it went for a long time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And after maybe a week or two weeks or 10 days, two the Red Cross nurses approached us, and-- not knowing what to do we-- the two of us were Jewish, and said, look we want-- we are saving young people.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We want to save you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And meanwhile, we befriended a girl called Krystyna, who was a Polish girl.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we want to befriend-- we want to save you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We'll put-- place the uniforms, Red Cross uniforms and caps, and-- and our identity cards in the pocket under the-- under the bench in the toilets.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you dress into it, go into big square, take who is coming out, go past the gate.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Remember-- memorize the name, your name, your name which should be like the nurse, and then go to the left and take to the disabled person to the hospital and come-- and disappear.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As luck would have it, my friend [?",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
